dhesi@cirrus.com (Rahul Dhesi) writes:

>This in fact is why I see no point in changing my login password every
>so often, as security-related documents often advise.  If I have a good
>password that hasn't yet been guessed, changing it hinders me . . .

Rahul is correct within the parameters he gives, but has missed a point.
The reason for changing passwords with some frequency is not to make them
more difficult to guess, but to ensure a limited lifetime to any compromised
password.
